**Summary of findings:**

- **Sotorasib** is the only treatment with a real PFS effect, and it is restricted to **KRAS G12C+ male** patients: delta ≈ +4.64–+5.0 months (p ≈ 0). In KRAS G12C+ females the effect collapses to delta ≈ −0.01 (p = 0.88). The treatment × sex interaction within KRAS+ has p ≈ 0; no additional 3-way modifier (STK11, ALK, BRCA2) is significant.
- **Pembrolizumab, olaparib, osimertinib** show no detectable PFS benefit in any subgroup tested — including their canonical biomarker matches (PDL1/TMB-high, BRCA2+, EGFR+).
- **Strong prognostic features** (independent of treatment): ECOG ↑, stage IV, brain mets, squamous histology, current smoking, weight loss → shorter PFS; never smoking and higher albumin → longer PFS. ALK fusion is a negative prognostic. Age has a counter-clinical positive coefficient in this synthetic cohort.

